  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patient is above 18 years old.

          2. The patient has enhanced solid mass of renal origin located in the kidney or elsewhere
             proved by imaging.

          3. Patient's mass size is up to 4cm at its largest dimension.

          4. Patient is able to visit the clinic as needed during the 60-month follow-up period
             following the cryoablation procedure.

          5. The patient has been informed of the study and agrees to its provisions, and has
             signed an IRB approved written informed consent, including data privacy authorization.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients with permanent coagulation disorders or severe medical instability or active
             infection.

          2. Patients with any terminal illness.

          3. Patient participating in other trials using drugs or devices.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
